A carpenter builds a wooden shelf bracket that is composed of two shapes, as shown.

\begin{itemize}
\item A rectangle with a length of $10$ centimeters and a height of $6$ centimeters.
\item A square with side length $4$ centimeters.
\end{itemize}

Find the total area, in square centimeters, of the bracket.

\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw (0,0) rectangle (2.5,1.5);
\draw (1.5,1.5) rectangle (2.5,2.5);
\node at (2.8,0.75) {6 cm};
\node at (1.25,-0.3) {10 cm};
\node at (2,2.75) {4 cm};
\end{tikzpicture}

\begin{enumerate}
\item[a.] $20$ square centimeters
\item[b.] $56$ square centimeters
\item[c.] $76$ square centimeters
\item[d.] $240$ square centimeters
\end{enumerate}
